contents.P:
The degree of milling for milled rice;
i.e.,
“hard milled,” “well-milled,” and “reasonably well-milled,” shall be equal to, or better than, that of the interpretive line samples for such rice.

P.text:
 Aromatic milled rice shall be special varieties of rice (Oryza
sativa L. scented) that have a distinctive and characteristic aroma;
e.g., basmati and jasmine rice.
